content:
### CSS Padding

**Padding** creates space between content and border.

---

### Individual Sides

```css
padding-top: 10px;
padding-right: 20px;
padding-bottom: 10px;
padding-left: 20px;
```

---

### Shorthand (1-4 Values)

```css
/* All sides */
padding: 20px;

/* Vertical | Horizontal */
padding: 10px 20px;

/* Top | Horizontal | Bottom */
padding: 10px 15px 20px;

/* Top | Right | Bottom | Left */
padding: 10px 15px 20px 25px;
```

**Memory trick:** Clockwise from top (Top, Right, Bottom, Left - TRBL).

---

### Values

```css
padding: 20px;       /* Fixed pixels */
padding: 1em;        /* Relative to font size */
padding: 5%;         /* Percentage of parent WIDTH */
padding: 1rem;       /* Relative to root font size */
```

**Important:** Percentage padding is based on **parent width**, not height.

---

### Padding Examples

```css
.button {
  padding: 12px 24px;  /* Comfortable button */
}

.card {
  padding: 20px;        /* Inner spacing */
}

.avatar {
  padding: 5px;         /* Tight spacing */
  border: 2px solid gray;
}
```

---

### Padding vs Margin

| Padding | Margin |
|---------|--------|
| Inside the border | Outside the border |
| Shows background color | Transparent |
| Cannot be negative | Can be negative |
| No collapsing | Collapses vertically |
| Part of clickable area | Not clickable |

---

### Accessibility with Padding

```css
/* Make links easier to click */
a {
  padding: 10px;  /* Larger click target */
}

/* Input padding for usability */
input {
  padding: 12px 16px;
}
```

> **Best Practice:** Use `padding` inside containers/cards/buttons. Don't use padding to create space between elements - use margin instead.
